Syntax: read <book>
Syntax: read chapter <chap. #> <book>
        read chapter <chap #>  (defaults to first book)

When you want to read something.  The <h> book system uses this
command to read the various books.  Some very long books have multiple
chapters.

Reading requires that you have a certain minimum intellect.

Programatically, read is usually the the same as "look at".  You may
discover that "read mail" will cause you to look at your chainMAIL boot
(or whatever).  Use the read 2.mail, 3.mail, etc method to distinguish the
proper one.  This should not happen with books

See Also: READ MAGIC, RECITE
Related Topics: OBJECT MANIPULATION
